Biscardi also recalled that "we came from a positive experience of exchanges with the Egyptian police, we were able to interrupt a few years before a traffic of migrants and the expectations on departure were to clarify the story. At first - he continued - there was an apparent collaboration, they allowed us to attend the assumptions of testimonies but we were looking for objective feedback. From the outset, the Egyptian authorities were informed that what had emerged from the autopsy carried out in Italy was not compatible with their investigative assumptions as the road accident."

