&nbsp;
Arcigay then reports the 32-year-old testimony: "I was just out of a bar and I was riding my bike when this person stood in front of me, he grabbed me for my hair and dropped me. He slapped me and punched me and then started insulting me."
&nbsp;
"These people - it is added - must be stopped, our community must wake up. Now I just want to find my serenity and have justice, for me and for all the victims like me." The commissioner of Arcigay Salerno, Francesco Napoli, said he had heard the 32-year-old and had "find a frightened and deeply shaken person. These episodes are part of that climate of violence and discrimination that is increasingly powerful in our country," he comments.

